<subSubSection id="C34E6519FFBAFFE5C5FAF9A2FDC1F97B" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BEB3692FFBAFFE5C5FAF9A2FDC1F97B" blockId="3.[151,1436,1573,1958]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">
<emphasis id="B920EA80FFBAFFE5C5FAF9A2FEA3F9C3" bold="true" box="[151,273,1573,1598]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male. In the group IV key of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC54B63FFBAFFE5C70BF9A2FC80F9C3" author="Borgmeier" box="[614,818,1573,1598]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" refString="Borgmeier, T. (1964) Revision of the North American phorid flies. Part II. The species of the genus Megaselia, subgenus Aphiochaeta. Studia Entomologica, 7, 257 - 416." type="journal article" year="1964">
Borgmeier (
<number id="3D9C24B5FFBAFFE5C783F9A2FC98F9C3" box="[750,810,1573,1598]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" value="1964.0">1964</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C544D11FFBAFFE5C653F9A1FC1FF9C0" box="[830,941,1573,1597]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bradyi">
<emphasis id="B920EA80FFBAFFE5C653F9A1FC1FF9C0" box="[830,941,1573,1597]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">M. bradyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
keys to couplet 
<number id="3D9C24B5FFBAFFE5C10AF9A1FB31F9C3" box="[1127,1155,1574,1598]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" value="17.0">17</number>
but differs from both 
<taxonomicName id="4C544D11FFBAFFE5C010F9A1FEFCF99F" authority="Malloch" authorityName="Malloch" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dificilis">
<emphasis id="B920EA80FFBAFFE5C010F9A1FF59F99C" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">M. dificilis</emphasis>
Malloch
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="4C544D11FFBAFFE5C41EF9CDFDDFF99F" authority="Borgmeier" authorityName="Borgmeier" box="[371,621,1609,1634]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cribella">
<emphasis id="B920EA80FFBAFFE5C41EF9CDFE5DF99C" box="[371,495,1609,1633]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">M. cribella</emphasis>
Borgmeier
</taxonomicName>
by having a characteristic basal fringe of 
<number id="3D9C24B5FFBAFFE5C12DF9CDFBEEF99F" box="[1088,1116,1610,1634]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" value="12.0">12</number>
+ robust, curved setae on the hind femur (F 
<number id="3D9C24B5FFBAFFE5C458F9E9FEF1F97B" box="[309,323,1646,1670]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454" value="3.0">3</number>
), which those species lack.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
